menu "Panda Hide (frida/debugger hiding)"

config PANDA_HIDE
	bool "Enable panda-hide (in-tree port of kpm-panda-hide)"
	depends on SECURITY
	depends on KPROBES
	depends on KALLSYMS
	depends on NET
	default y
	help
	  In-tree port of https://github.com/P4nda0s/kpm-panda-hide

	  Original project is a KernelPatch KPM module. This option builds an
	  equivalent built-in implementation using:
	    - kprobe/kretprobe for /proc and memory scrubbing hooks
	    - LSM hooks for path open and socket connect filtering

	  Features:
	    - Hide TracerPid / tracing-stop / ptrace_stop / task state 't'
	    - Hide frida-related /proc/pid/maps entries and thread names
	    - Return -ENOENT for frida agent/gadget paths
	    - Refuse connect() to common frida ports (except adbd)
	    - Scrub frida signatures from access_remote_vm read buffers

	  If unsure, say Y for security-research / reverse-engineering builds.

config PANDA_HIDE_LSM_ORDER
	bool "Append panda_hide to default CONFIG_LSM string at build time"
	depends on PANDA_HIDE
	default y
	help
	  When enabled, the integration script appends ",panda_hide" to
	  CONFIG_LSM. Required for LSM path/net hooks to load.

endmenu
